Sponges, compound or solitary ascidians, soft coral or actinians occasionally, bivalve shells rarely (see discussion under Shell-carrying behaviour), fragments of weed. Some dromiine members (
Epigodromia
,
Takedromia
), with small last pereopods, are not known to carry any camouflage ( Wicksten 1986a: 364 ; McLay 1993: 213 , 216, 219, 224; 2001b: 7; Guinot et al . 1995: 385, 401;
Ng et al . 2000: 157
).

